article.headline: Ill.-Chicago 74, Murray St. 68
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Othyus Jeffers scored 16 points and had nine rebounds to lead five Illinois-Chicago players in double-figure scoring as the Flames topped Murray State 74-68 Tuesday night. Stewart Spencer and Robert Bush added 12 points each for Illinois-Chicago (3-4), while Scott Vandermeer and T.J. Gray chipped in 11 and 10 apiece, respectively. Spencer, Bush and Gray combined to go 10-for-10 from the foul line. The Racers (2-5) were led by 19 points and nine rebounds from Shawn Witherspoon, who was 4-for-6 from three-point range. Ed Horton added 11 points. Murray State shot 50 percent in the first half -- when they led by as many as 13 points -- and held Illinois-Chicago to just 6-of-23 (26 percent) shooting to take a 38-27 lead into halftime. But the Flames bounced back with 58 percent second-half shooting and held the Racers to just 31 percent after the break. Illinois-Chicago also capitalized on Murray State mistakes, scoring 19 points off turnovers.
